{
  "texts": [
    "This study (Naik et al, 2022) examines the effectiveness of DL and ML techniques for classifying chilli leaf disease.",
    "Twelve pre-trained DL networks were employed, and the dataset features images of five critical diseases.",
    "Without augmentation, VGG19 had the highest accuracy (83.54%), whereas DarkNet53 performed exceptionally well with augmentation.",
    "A unique squeeze-and-excitation-based convolutional neural network (SECNN) model outperformed the rest, obtaining 98.63% accuracy without augmentation and 99.12% with augmentation, respectively (Table 6).",
    "This research examines the prevalence of pests and diseases in growing chili peppers, a vital vegetable crop worldwide."
  ]
}